To install Armadillo we need: LAPACK, BLAS/OpenBLAS, ARPACK and SuperLU. 

Dortran:
sudo apt-get install gfortran

==========LINHAS:
sudo apt-get install gfortran
git clone https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS.git
git checkout develop
mkdir build
cd build/
cmake ../
sudo apt update
apt search openblas
sudo apt install libopenblas-dev
sudo update-alternatives --config libblas.so.3

export OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=4
export GOTO_NUM_THREADS=4
export OMP_NUM_THREADS=4

make
make install ---> aqui falo do openblas

==========

Openblas -http://www.openblas.net/
git clone https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS.git
cd OpenBLAS
git checkout master
mkdir build
cmake ../
make
sudo make install



Openblas - DEV
mkdir dev
cd dev
git clone https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS.git
cd OpenBLAS
git checkout develop
mkdir build
cmake ../
make
sudo make install

====https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS/wiki/Precompiled-installation-packages

LAPACK -http://www.netlib.org/lapack/
git clone https://github.com/Reference-LAPACK/lapack
cd lapack
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ../ CFLAGS=-fPIC CXXFLAGS=-fPIC LFLAGS=-fPIC cmake ../
make
sudo make install


LAPACK RELAESE
git clone https://github.com/Reference-LAPACK/lapack-release.git
cd lapack-release
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ../
make
sudo make install


SUPERLU
git clone https://github.com/xiaoyeli/superlu.git
cd superlu
mkdir build
cd build
CFLAGS=-fPIC CXXFLAGS=-fPIC LFLAGS=-fPIC cmake ../
make
sudo make install



ARPACK-NG
First: sudo apt-get install autoconf


git clone https://github.com/opencollab/arpack-ng.git
cd arpack-ng/
sh bootstrap
./configure
make
make check
sudo make install

